Cleaning up resources is essential to avoid unnecessary costs in Azure. Deleting a resource group removes all resources within it.

Steps:

1. Go to Azure Portal
2. Navigate to Resource Groups
3. Select the resource group
4. Click “Delete Resource Group”
5. Confirm by typing the name
6. Click Delete

For example, after completing a lab exercise, deleting the resource group ensures no charges are incurred.

A real-life use case is temporary testing environments that are created and deleted frequently.

Another example is cost optimization, where unused resources are removed to reduce billing.

This exercise teaches responsible cloud usage.
